0,/Hotel_Review-g186338-d11621939-Reviews-or0-Novotel_London_Canary_Wharf-London_England.html#REVIEWS,Novotel London Canary Wharf Hotel Reviews,Great facilities but poor service,"Before Covid, I used to stay regularly and every other week and I was very much looking forward to returning as it was always a firm favourite and my go to whenever in London. I have stayed across all rooms categories previously.   Pros:  1. Great facilities and very clean. Gym and pool facilities are excellent although I did not visit on this occasion.  2. If you like a room with a view, definitely ask for a city view room on a high floor. Although you do pay a significant premium for this.   3. Highly recommend the executive suites if you find a deal. Executive rooms no longer have lounge access.   Cons 1. Check in is slow. I normally book same day and although I received a confirmation email, it never seems to fully transfer to the reservation system so it needs to be recreated manually. Overall check in took 10 minutes despite being first in the queue. I think this is an issue with Accor system rather than the hotel itself.   2. Loyalty does not seem to be recognised. No acknowledgement of Accor loyalty status at all which is disappointing on my first return stay after Covid absence. No complimentary water in rooms and none in fridge. I was asked whether I stayed here before despite staying approximately 12 times previously.   3. Avoid the rooftop bar Bokan at all costs. While the view is amazing, the service is appalling. I made a reservation for the bar and was seated. Despite being a relatively quiet mid week evening, my order wasn‚Äôt taken for about 20 minutes. There was no apology for the wait and while I was extremely polite to the waiter, I watched the drinks being made and they sat there for another 8-10 minutes before the waiter delivered them to the table. Empty glasses were sat on my table for another 20 minutes and not one waiter came over to ask if we wanted anything else. I also asked for a water which never arrived. While I was seated, the table need to me ordered two bottle of champagne and the waiter came up to them approximately 12 times to top their glasses up but never once came over to us despite trying to get his attention. I had planned to spend money on here but clearly they were not interested so after an hour I left disappointed. No thank you or goodbye by any of the staff I walked past. A round of drinks for 2 came in at ¬£30 including service charge which I felt annoyed at paying for the ‚Äòservice‚Äô  In the end, I went back to my room and ordered a drink on room service which was another 20 minutes. It seems the strategy here is to make ignore the majority of guests and focus on the ‚Äòbig spenders‚Äô clientele.   4. I didn‚Äôt have breakfast on this occasion so cannot comment. I usually avoid the ¬£25 breakfast as previously the hot breakfast has been cold and disappointing. If you want breakfast, I would recommend ordering it as room service to ensure it is freshly cooked to order.   Overall I was disappointed and don‚Äôt think I will return here. There are cheaper hotels with a far better service‚Ä¶",Date of stay: April 2021,2.0
